The button component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-button</span>, is used to style &lt;button&gt; tags. Note that all optional classes may be used in combination with each other, for example on a single element with <span class="gds-text--code">gds-button--success</span>, <span class="gds-text--code">gds-button--lg</span>, & <span class="gds-text--code">gds-button--block</span> classes. To indicate that a button is disabled, use the disabled="disabled" HTML attribute.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Button

@name {String} name Button

@example {Code}

<button class="gds-button gds-button--default">Default button</button>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Dan McKenna, Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-button
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-button
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses gds-button--default,gds-button--lg,gds-button--sm,gds-button--xs,gds-button--primary,gds-button--secondary,gds-button--success,gds-button--warning,gds-button--info,gds-button--danger,gds-button--link,gds-button--block

The link component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-text--link</span>, is used to style text links.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Link

@name {String} name Link

@example {Code}

<a class="gds-text--link" href="#">A text link</a>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-text--link
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-text--link
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

The loading component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading</span>, is used to indicate asynchronous loading of content. To show the indicator on a transparent overlay, add the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading--bg</span> class to the parent element containing <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading</span>.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Loading

@name {String} name Loading

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-loading">
---]<div class="gds-loading__dot"></div>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-loading
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-loading
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

For a larger variation of <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading</span>, add the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading__dot--lg</span> class to <span class="gds-text--code">gds-loading__dot</span>.

@section {String} section Atoms

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Loading

@name {String} name Loading - Large

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-loading">
---]<div class="gds-loading__dot gds-loading__dot--lg"></div>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-loading--lg
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-loading
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

The corner-content component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-corner-content</span>, is meant for secondary navigation that does not work in the context of a standard <span class="gds-text--code">gds-modal</span> component. To show the component, add the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-corner-content--shown</span> class to <span class="gds-text--code">gds-corner-content</span>. This component can be aligned to the right or left side of the user's window by toggling the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-corner-content--right</span> and <span class="gds-text--code">gds-corner-content--left</span> classes.

@section {String} section Molecules

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Corner-Content

@name {String} name Corner-Content

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-corner-content gds-corner-content--right gds-corner-content--shown">
---]<div class="gds-corner-content__header">
---]---]<h4 class="gds-corner-content__title">Corner content title</h4>
---]---]<div class="gds-corner-content__controls">
---]---]---]<button class="gds-corner-content__button"><i class="fa fa-arrows-h"></i></button>
---]---]---]<button class="gds-corner-content__button"><i class="fa fa-expand"></i></button>
---]---]</div>
---]</div>
---]<div class="gds-corner-content__block">
---]---]...
---]</div>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup false

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-corner-content

@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses gds-corner-content--shown,gds-corner-content--left,gds-corner-content--right

The avatar component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-avatar</span>, can display a user's photo, a brand's logo, or a flag icon for internationalization. The avatar can include a dropdown menu, which is meant to be shown when the avatar is clicked on. To show the dropdown menu, add the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-avatar--menu-open</span> class to <span class="gds-text--code">gds-avatar</span>.

@section {String} section Molecules

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Avatar

@name {String} name Avatar

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-avatar">
---]<div class="gds-avatar__image">
---]---]<img src="https://ds.gumgum.com/images/ken.png" alt="Ken Weiner" height="100%" />
---]</div>
---]<div class="gds-avatar__menu">
---]---]<ul class="gds-avatar__menu-list">
---]---]---]<li class="gds-avatar__menu-list-item -ellipsis"><a class="gds-avatar__menu-list-link" href="#">Profile</a></li>
---]---]---]<li class="gds-avatar__menu-list-item -ellipsis"><a class="gds-avatar__menu-list-link" href="#">Settings</a></li>
---]---]---]<li class="gds-avatar__menu-list-divider"></li>
---]---]---]<li class="gds-avatar__menu-list-item -ellipsis"><a class="gds-avatar__menu-list-link" href="#">Logout</a></li>
---]---]</ul>
---]</div>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Dan McKenna, Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-avatar
@defaultClasses {Array} defaultClasses gds-avatar
@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

The HTML-preview component, prefixed by <span class="gds-text--code">gds-html-preview</span> is a stage for displaying HTML content on a simulated transparent background.

@section {String} section Molecules

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent HTML Preview

@name {String} name HTML Preview

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-html-preview">
---]<iframe class="gds-html-preview__content" frameborder="0" scrolling="0"></iframe>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Dan McKenna, Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger gds-html-preview

@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses gds-html-preview--active,gds-html-preview--disabled,gds-html-preview--resize

To indicate <span class="gds-text--regular">positive</span> (green), <span class="gds-text--regular">neutral</span> (yellow), or <span class="gds-text--regular">negative</span> (red) states on a table cell, use the <span class="gds-text--code">gds-table__cell--positive</span>, <span class="gds-text--code">gds-table__cell--neutral</span> & <span class="gds-text--code">gds-table__cell--negative</span> classes.

@section {String} section Molecules

@parentComponent {String} parentComponent Table

@name {String} name Table - Colored Cells

@example {Code}

<div class="gds-table--responsive">
---]<table class="gds-table">
---]---]<thead>
---]---]---]<tr class="gds-table__row">
---]---]---]---]<th class="gds-table__header">#</th>
---]---]---]---]<th class="gds-table__header -text-left">First Name</th>
---]---]---]---]<th class="gds-table__header -text-left">Last Name</th>
---]---]---]---]<th class="gds-table__header gds-table__header--selected -text-left">Username (selected)</th>
---]---]---]</tr>
---]---]</thead>
---]---]<tbody>
---]---]---]<tr class="gds-table__row">
---]---]---]---]<th scope="row">1</th>
---]---]---]---]<td class="gds-table__cell--positive">Mark</td>
---]---]---]---]<td class="gds-table__cell--neutral">Otto</td>
---]---]---]---]<td class="gds-table__cell--negative">@mdo</td>
---]---]---]</tr>
---]---]</tbody>
---]</table>
</div>

@renderMarkup {Boolean} renderMarkup true

@author {String} author Myles O'Connor

@tabTrigger {String} tabTrigger

@optionalClasses {Array} optionalClasses

